Subject is known to be deceased
AllowableCodes:
0 = Not deceased/unknown
1 = Deceased
Description/derivation:	A subject with a Neuropathology Form and/or a Milestones Form reporting the subject's death is indicated as deceased (naccdied = 1). Otherwise, naccdied = 0. NOTE: NACC is not always made aware of deaths for active and inactive subjects; thus naccdied = 0 for a subject who has died but whose death was not reported to NACC.

ShortDescriptor: Does the subject report a decline in memory (relative to previously attained abilities)?
AllowableCodes:
0 = No		 
1 = Yes
8 = Could not be assessed/subject too impaired 
9= Unknown
Description/derivation 	Note that "Could not be assessed/subject too impaired" (decsub = 8) was added in UDS3 and was not an available option in versions 1- 2. 
		Please note that in version 1.2 of the UDS, the follow-up visit form asked for changes since the previous visit. If "No meaningful changes" (b9chg = 1) was selected, the clinician did not complete the rest of the form. In these cases, NACC has brought forward data from the previous visit. In cases where changes were reported on the form, the new data are provided longitudinally as recorded by the clinician. These changes apply only to those subjects who had a UDS follow-up visit using version 1.2 of the UDS (2005 - 2008); data collected using versions 2 and 3 of the UDS are not affected by this change.
